    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing null terminator in PDCP layer cleanup\n\n### Summary\nThere is a missing null terminator on a string buffer leading to out-of-bounds read downstream of function pdcp_layer_cleanup in openair2/LAYER2/PDCP_v10.1.0/pdcp.c. When calling pdcp_layer_cleanup() the behavior is not what is expected. The issue may be in pdcp_layer_cleanup or a function downstream/upstream of it.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/PDCP_v10.1.0/pdcp.c`: Enhanced pdcp_layer_cleanup() to properly reinitialize global data structures after cleanup, ensuring all memory is in a known state to prevent out-of-bounds reads.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain conditions where pdcp_layer_cleanup is called followed by downstream functions that access PDCP global state, a segfault may occur due to accessing uninitialized memory that appears as a non-null-terminated string buffer. Memory inspection shows reads past intended buffer boundaries in functions that process PDCP statistics or MBMS data after cleanup.\n"
}